id: pm-z9ho
title: PmPackageResourceKind is missing 'assets' and 'prompts' as canonical resource types
description: "src/core/packages/manifest.ts defines PM_PACKAGE_RESOURCE_KINDS = ['extensions', 'docs', 'examples']. The EXTENSIONS.md docs note that 'agent-specific assets such as prompts, skills, or MCP servers should live in agent adapter packages, not in the core pm package contract.' But there is no canonical resource kind for prompts or assets. The pm-claude plugin ships skills and slash-command markdown under plugins/pm-claude/ with no pm package manifest resources entry. Adding 'prompts' and 'assets' as optional resource kinds would let package authors declare and discover these resources via assertPackageManifest, smoke harness, and package doctor, enabling a richer marketplace catalog."
type: Feature
status: open
priority: 3
tags[4]: "area:packages","area:sdk",extensibility,marketplace
created_at: "2026-06-07T10:05:30.744Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-07T10:22:15.341Z"
